                  "kind": "text",
                  "data": "Done. I've created `docs/implementation-plan.md` with **28 tasks across 7 phases**. Here's the summary:\n\n## Plan Overview\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Focus | Key Risk |\n|-------|-------|-------|----------|\n| 1 (Foundation) | Tasks 1–7 | Gradle, Hilt, Retrofit, theme, auth, navigation shell | Package rename |\n| 2 (Appointments) | Tasks 8–10 | API, list/detail, booking wizard | None (straightforward) |\n| 3 (Catalog) | Tasks 11–13 | Room cache, product grid, detail | Offline sync logic |\n| 4 (AR) | Tasks 14–16 | CameraX, MediaPipe, frame overlay | **Highest risk** — FPS/device compat |\n| 5 (Orders) | Tasks 17–20 | Order request, list/detail, billing | None |\n| 6 (Prescriptions/Chat/Feedback) | Tasks 21–24 | Three independent features | File upload multipart |\n| 7 (Home/Polish) | Tasks 25–28 | Dashboard, profile, error states, demo prep | Integration bugs |\n\n## Key Design Choices\n\n- **AR in Phase 4** (not later) — fail fast on the highest-risk capstone hook\n- **Home screen in Phase 7** (not Phase 2) — it aggregates data from appointments, orders, prescriptions, and products, so it's built last when all repos exist\n- **Vertical slicing** — each task delivers a testable end-to-end piece (API → repo → ViewModel → screen)\n- **Every task ≤ M size** — no task touches more than ~8 files\n\n## Open Questions for You\n\n1. Is the backend's `ar_asset_reference` a full URL or relative path?\n2. Are products behind auth or publicly accessible?\n3. What seeded demo data already exists on the backend?\n\nWant me to start implementing Task 1 (Gradle scaffolding)?"
